<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05001m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05001m">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05001m"> 1(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nephews of S. Martin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The history of <i>Les Sept-Dormants</i> of Marmoutier must be distinguished from that of <i>Les Sept-Dormants</i> of Ephesus in St. Gregory of Tours &hellip; The seven brothers of Marmoutier, according to Dom. Mart&egrave;ne, were <mark>nephews of St. Martin</mark>, and consequently cousins of St. Patrick. <small> William Bullen Morris, <a name="WBML" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WBML"><cite title="source">The Life of Saint Patrick Apostle of Ireland</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1890) 87n</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Saint Patrick was reputedly a nephew of Saint Martin of Tours (4th century). </mm> </dd></dl>
